---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Acceptable Use Policy"
  description="Natred's acceptable use policy governing proper use of IT services, prohibited activities, and enforcement procedures."
>
  <HeroSection
    title="Acceptable Use Policy"
    subtitle="Guidelines for using our services"
    compact={true}
    showCta={false}
  />

  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="policy-content">
        <div class="policy-intro animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 2026</p>
          <p class="intro-text">This Acceptable Use Policy ("AUP") governs the use of IT services, systems, and resources provided by Avian Forge (Pty) Ltd, trading as Natred. By using our Services, you agree to comply with this policy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>1. Purpose</h2>
          <p>This policy exists to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Protect our clients, systems, and reputation</li>
            <li>Ensure fair and reliable service for all clients</li>
            <li>Comply with applicable laws and regulations</li>
            <li>Prevent misuse that could harm others</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>2. Permitted Use</h2>
          <p>Our Services may be used for lawful business purposes consistent with your agreement with us. This includes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Normal business operations and communications</li>
            <li>Data processing and storage within agreed parameters</li>
            <li>Use of hosted services and applications as intended</li>
            <li>Development and testing in designated environments</li>
            <li>Collaboration and file sharing with authorized parties</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>3. Prohibited Activities</h2>
          <p>The following activities are strictly prohibited:</p>

          <h3>3.1 Illegal Activities</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Any activity that violates South African law or the laws of other applicable jurisdictions</li>
            <li>Fraud, identity theft, or financial crimes</li>
            <li>Distribution of illegal content including child exploitation material</li>
            <li>Intellectual property infringement</li>
            <li>Privacy violations or unauthorised data collection</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.2 Security Violations</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Unauthorized access or attempts to access systems, accounts, or data</li>
            <li>Distribution of malware, viruses, or other harmful code</li>
            <li>Attempting to circumvent security measures</li>
            <li>Port scanning, vulnerability scanning, or network probing without authorization</li>
            <li>Denial of service attacks or activities that degrade network performance</li>
            <li>Sharing of credentials or unauthorised credential harvesting</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.3 Abuse of Resources</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Using Services to send spam, bulk unsolicited messages, or phishing attempts</li>
            <li>Cryptocurrency mining without explicit agreement</li>
            <li>Excessive resource consumption that impacts other clients</li>
            <li>Reselling or redistributing Services without authorization</li>
            <li>Using Services to operate open proxies or relays</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.4 Harmful Content</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Content that promotes violence, hatred, or discrimination</li>
            <li>Harassment, stalking, or threatening behavior</li>
            <li>Defamatory content</li>
            <li>Content that exploits minors</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.5 Misrepresentation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Impersonating others or misrepresenting your identity</li>
            <li>Falsifying headers, sender information, or routing data</li>
            <li>Operating services under false pretenses</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>4. Security Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>Clients are responsible for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Maintaining security of their credentials and access tokens</li>
            <li>Keeping software patched and up to date (unless managed by us)</li>
            <li>Reporting suspected security incidents promptly</li>
            <li>Implementing appropriate access controls for their users</li>
            <li>Securing any devices that connect to managed networks</li>
            <li>Complying with security policies provided as part of our Services</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>5. Resource Limits</h2>
          <p>To ensure fair service for all clients:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>We may implement reasonable usage limits on storage, bandwidth, or processing</li>
            <li>Specific limits will be communicated in your service agreement</li>
            <li>We will notify you if usage approaches limits and discuss options</li>
            <li>Activities that negatively impact other clients may be throttled or suspended</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>6. Monitoring</h2>
          <p>We may monitor Services to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Ensure compliance with this policy</li>
            <li>Protect system integrity and security</li>
            <li>Respond to legal requirements</li>
            <li>Troubleshoot technical issues</li>
            <li>Improve service quality</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We do not routinely monitor content but may investigate upon receiving complaints or detecting anomalies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>7. Enforcement</h2>
          <h3>7.1 Violations</h3>
          <p>If we identify or receive a credible report of a policy violation, we may:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Issue a warning and request remediation</li>
            <li>Temporarily suspend affected services</li>
            <li>Require removal of offending content or cessation of activity</li>
            <li>Permanently terminate services for serious or repeated violations</li>
            <li>Report illegal activity to appropriate authorities</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>7.2 Process</h3>
          <p>For non-urgent violations, we will generally:</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Notify you of the suspected violation</li>
            <li>Provide opportunity to explain or remediate (typically 48-72 hours)</li>
            <li>Take action based on the response and severity</li>
          </ol>
          <p>For urgent situations (active attacks, illegal content, immediate harm), we may act immediately without prior notice.</p>

          <h3>7.3 Appeals</h3>
          <p>If you believe enforcement action was taken in error, contact us within 14 days with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Details of the action taken</li>
            <li>Your explanation of the circumstances</li>
            <li>Evidence supporting your position</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We will review and respond within 10 business days.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>8. Reporting Violations</h2>
          <p>If you become aware of any violation of this policy, please report it to:</p>
          <div class="contact-info">
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:service@natred.com">service@natred.com</a></p>
            <p><strong>Subject line:</strong> AUP Violation Report</p>
          </div>
          <p>Please include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Description of the suspected violation</li>
            <li>Date and time observed</li>
            <li>Any relevant evidence or logs</li>
            <li>Your contact information for follow-up</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>We may update this policy to reflect changes in our services, legal requirements, or industry practices. Material changes will be communicated with at least 30 days' notice. Continued use of Services after changes take effect constitutes acceptance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>10. Questions</h2>
          <p>If you have questions about what is or isn't permitted, please ask before proceeding:</p>
          <div class="contact-info">
            <p><strong>Avian Forge (Pty) Ltd (trading as Natred)</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:service@natred.com">service@natred.com</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .policy-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .policy-intro {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
    padding-bottom: 30px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--dark-gray);
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--natred-orange);
    font-size: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .intro-text {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .policy-section {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    padding-bottom: 40px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--dark-gray);
  }

  .policy-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .policy-section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .policy-section h3 {
    font-size: 18px;
    margin-top: 25px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .policy-section p {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  .policy-section ul,
  .policy-section ol {
    margin-top: 15px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .policy-section li {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    padding-left: 25px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .policy-section ul li::before {
    content: '\2022';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--natred-orange);
  }

  .policy-section ol {
    counter-reset: list-counter;
  }

  .policy-section ol li {
    counter-increment: list-counter;
  }

  .policy-section ol li::before {
    content: counter(list-counter) ".";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--natred-orange);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .policy-section li strong {
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .contact-info {
    background: var(--charcoal);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--natred-orange);
    margin-top: 15px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  .contact-info p {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .contact-info p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .contact-info a {
    color: var(--natred-orange);
    transition: color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .contact-info a:hover {
    color: var(--white);
  }
</style>
